TITLE: Initializing Multiple Rspack Configurations with MultiCompiler
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use Rspack's JavaScript API to run multiple configurations in separate compilers. The callback is called after all compilers have been executed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/compiler.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { rspack } = require('@rspack/core');

rspack(
  [
    { entry: './index1.js', output: { filename: 'bundle1.js' } },
    { entry: './index2.js', output: { filename: 'bundle2.js' } },
  ],
  (err, stats) => {
    process.stdout.write(stats.toString() + '\n');
  },
);
```

