TITLE: Implementing a Custom Plugin in Rspack using Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a custom plugin in Rspack using the `plugin` and `plugin_hook` macros. It shows the structure of a plugin, how to define a hook, and implement the `Plugin` trait.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/contribute/architecture/builtin-plugin.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use rspack_hook::{plugin, plugin_hook};
use rspack_core::{Plugin, PluginContext, ApplyContext, CompilerOptions};
use rspack_core::CompilerCompilation;
use rspack_error::Result;

// define the plugin
#[plugin]
pub struct MyPlugin {
  options: MyPluginOptions
}

// define the plugin hook
#[plugin_hook(CompilerCompilation for MyPlugin)]
async fn compilation(&self, compilation: &mut Compilation) -> Result<()> {
  // do something...
}

// implement apply method for the plugin
impl Plugin for MyPlugin {
  fn apply(&self, ctx: PluginContext<&mut ApplyContext>, _options: &mut CompilerOptions) -> Result<()> {
    ctx.context.compiler_hooks.tap(compilation::new(self))
    Ok(())
  }
}
```

