TITLE: Configuring Lazy Compilation with Entries and Imports
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a more explicit way to configure lazy compilation in Rspack by setting the `entries` and `imports` options within `experiments.lazyCompilation`.  This allows for fine-grained control over which parts of the application are lazily compiled. Specifically, it enables lazy compilation for both entry points and dynamic imports.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/features/lazy-compilation.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js title="rspack.config.mjs"
import { defineConfig } from '@rspack/cli';

export default defineConfig({
  entry: {
    Home: './src/Home.js',
    About: './src/About.js',
  },
  experiments: {
    lazyCompilation: {
      // lazy compile entries
      entries: true,
      // lazy compile dynamic imports
      imports: true,
    },
  },
});
```
```

