TITLE: Creating a Custom Plugin in Rspack
DESCRIPTION: Provides the structure for authoring a custom Rspack plugin, implementing an `apply` method that interacts with the Rspack compiler using hooks. Ideal for leveraging Rspack's low-level build processes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/features/plugin.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const PLUGIN_NAME = 'MyPlugin';

export class MyPlugin {
  apply(compiler) {
    compiler.hooks.compilation.tap(PLUGIN_NAME, compilation => {
      console.log('The Rspack build process is starting!');
    });
  }
}
```

