TITLE: Configuring Entry Points and Chunk Splitting in Webpack
DESCRIPTION: This Webpack configuration file defines entry points for three pages (`pageA`, `pageB`, and `pageC`) while employing splitChunks optimization to separate common modules and vendor libraries into distinct bundles. It requires Node.js and Webpack installed. Key parameters include entry points declaring the main modules for each page, and optimization settings that specify splitting strategies for common utilities and vendor code. The output is configured to generate named JavaScript files for each entry point and chunk.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/common-chunk-and-vendor-chunk/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var path = require("path");

module.exports = {
	// mode: "development" || "production",
	entry: {
		pageA: "./pageA",
		pageB: "./pageB",
		pageC: "./pageC"
	},
	optimization: {
		chunkIds: "named",
		splitChunks: {
			cacheGroups: {
				commons: {
					chunks: "initial",
					minChunks: 2,
					maxInitialRequests: 5, // The default limit is too small to showcase the effect
					minSize: 0 // This is example is too small to create commons chunks
				},
				vendor: {
					test: /node_modules/,
					chunks: "initial",
					name: "vendor",
					priority: 10,
					enforce: true
				}
			}
		}
	},
	output: {
		path: path.join(__dirname, "dist"),
		filename: "[name].js"
	}
};
```

