TITLE: Using Module Federation v1.5 with Runtime SDK
DESCRIPTION: Example of using Module Federation dynamically without compile-time plugins using the @module-federation/runtime-tools package. This approach initializes the federation runtime with remote modules and shared dependencies, and demonstrates how to load remote modules at runtime.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/blog/module-federation-added-to-rspack.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Can load modules using only the runtime SDK without relying on build plugins
// When not using build plugins, shared dependencies cannot be automatically reused
import { init, loadRemote } from '@module-federation/runtime-tools';
import customPlugin from './runtimePlugin';

init({
  name: 'app1',
  remotes: [
    {
      name: 'runtime_remote1',
      alias: 'app2',
      entry: 'http://localhost:3006/remoteEntry.js',
    },
  ],
  shared: {
    react: {
      version: '18.2.0',
      scope: 'default',
      lib: () => React,
      shareConfig: {
        singleton: true,
        requiredVersion: '>17',
      },
    },
    'react-dom': {
      version: '18.2.0',
      scope: 'default',
      lib: () => ReactDOM,
      shareConfig: {
        singleton: true,
        requiredVersion: '>17',
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [customPlugin()],
});

// Load by alias
loadRemote <
  { add: (...args: Array<number>) => number } >
  'app2/util'.then(md => {
    md.add(1, 2, 3);
  });
```

