TITLE: Integrating Lazy Compilation Middleware with Custom Server
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates how to integrate Rspack's lazy compilation middleware into a custom development server using `webpack-dev-server`. It demonstrates how to obtain the middleware and insert it into the server's middleware stack, enabling lazy compilation for custom server setups. It requires `@rspack/core` and `webpack-dev-server`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/features/lazy-compilation.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js title="start.mjs"
import { experiments, rspack } from '@rspack/core';
import config from './rspack.config.mjs';
import DevServer from 'webpack-dev-server';

const compiler = rspack(config);

const middleware = experiments.lazyCompilationMiddleware(
  compiler,
  config.experiments.lazyCompilation,
);

const server = new DevServer(
  {
    port: 3000,
    setupMiddlewares(other) {
      return [middleware, ...other];
    },
  },
  compiler,
);

server.start();
```
```

