TITLE: DefinePlugin TypeScript Type Definitions
DESCRIPTION: Defines the TypeScript types used by the DefinePlugin for its options. It shows the structure of code values that can be used for replacements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/plugins/webpack/define-plugin.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type CodeValue = RecursiveArrayOrRecord<CodeValuePrimitive>;
type CodeValuePrimitive =
  | null
  | undefined
  | RegExp
  | Function
  | string
  | number
  | boolean
  | bigint
  | undefined;
type RecursiveArrayOrRecord<T> =
  | { [index: string]: RecursiveArrayOrRecord<T> }
  | Array<RecursiveArrayOrRecord<T>>
  | T;

type DefinePluginOptions = Record<string, CodeValue>;
```

