TITLE: Updating an Existing Asset in Rspack
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to update an existing asset 'main.js' by replacing its content with new source code and setting the minimized flag. Requires the asset to already exist or an error will be thrown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/compilation.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
updateAsset(
  filename: string, // filename of the updating asset
  source: Source | ((source: Source) => Source), // the new content or a function returns the new content
  info?:  // the new info or a function returns the new info
    | AssetInfo
    | ((assetInfo: AssetInfo) => AssetInfo)
): void;
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
compiler.hooks.thisCompilation.tap('MyPlugin', compilation => {
  const { RawSource } = compiler.webpack.sources;
  compilation.hooks.processAssets.tap('MyPlugin', () => {
    const updatedSource = new RawSource(
      `module.exports = "This is the updated"`,
    );
    compilation.updateAsset('main.js', updatedSource, {
      minimized: true,
    });
  });
});
```

