TITLE: Comprehensive Error Handling
DESCRIPTION: Complete example of handling different types of errors including fatal errors, compilation errors, and warnings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { rspack } from '@rspack/core';

rspack(
  {
    // ...
  },
  (err, stats) => {
    if (err) {
      console.error(err.stack || err);
      if (err.details) {
        console.error(err.details);
      }
      return;
    }

    const info = stats.toJson();

    if (stats.hasErrors()) {
      console.error(info.errors);
    }

    if (stats.hasWarnings()) {
      console.warn(info.warnings);
    }

    // Log result...
  },
);
```

