TITLE: Updating Lazy-Loaded Module in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code updates a lazy-loaded module 'module.js'. It sets up hot module replacement for the lazy-loaded module, including accept and dispose handlers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/packages/rspack-test-tools/tests/hotCases/lazy-compilation/context/__snapshots__/web/2.snap.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
self["webpackHotUpdate"]('modules_module_js_lazy-compilation-proxy', {
"./modules/module.js!lazy-compilation-proxy": 
/*!***********************************************************************************************************************!*\
  !*** lazy-compilation-proxy|../../../../../dist/helper/loaders/hot-update.js??ruleSet[1].rules[0].use[0]!./module.js ***!
