TITLE: Adding Attributes to Script Tags with alterAssetTags Hook in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the alterAssetTags hook to add a 'specialAttribute' to all script tags. This demonstrates how to modify asset tags before they are inserted into the HTML.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/plugins/rspack/html-rspack-plugin.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const AddAttributePlugin = {
  apply(compiler) {
    compiler.hooks.compilation.tap('AddAttributePlugin', compilation => {
      HtmlRspackPlugin.getCompilationHooks(
        compilation,
      ).alterAssetTags.tapPromise('AddAttributePlugin', async data => {
        data.assetTags.scripts = data.assetTags.scripts.map(tag => {
          if (tag.tagName === 'script') {
            tag.attributes.specialAttribute = true;
          }
          return tag;
        });
      });
    });
  },
};

export default {
  //...
  plugins: [new HtmlRspackPlugin(), AddAttributePlugin],
};
```

