TITLE: Conditional Self-Accepting of Module Updates in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a scenario where a module self-accepts updates but invalidates itself when certain conditions are not met. This pattern is useful for modules with constant values that shouldn't change.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/zh/api/runtime-api/hmr.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const VALUE = 'constant';

export default VALUE;

if (
  module.hot.data &&
  module.hot.data.value &&
  module.hot.data.value !== VALUE
) {
  module.hot.invalidate();
} else {
  module.hot.dispose(data => {
    data.value = VALUE;
  });
  module.hot.accept();
}
```

