TITLE: Loading WebAssembly Modules in Webpack
DESCRIPTION: This function handles loading WebAssembly modules. It supports both streaming instantiation and fallback to arrayBuffer instantiation for older browsers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/wasm-complex/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
__webpack_require__.v = (exports, wasmModuleId, wasmModuleHash, importsObj) => {
	var req = fetch(__webpack_require__.p + "" + wasmModuleHash + ".module.wasm");
	if (typeof WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming === 'function') {
		return WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming(req, importsObj)
			.then((res) => (Object.assign(exports, res.instance.exports)));
	}
	return req
		.then((x) => (x.arrayBuffer()))
		.then((bytes) => (WebAssembly.instantiate(bytes, importsObj)))
		.then((res) => (Object.assign(exports, res.instance.exports)));
};
```

