TITLE: Processing New Assets with Cache in Rspack Plugin
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to track newly added assets using the cache API in a Rspack plugin's processAssets hook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/cache.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
compiler.hooks.compilation.tap('MyPlugin', compilation => {
  compilation.hooks.processAssets.tapPromise('MyPlugin', async () => {
    const cache = compilation.getCache('MyPlugin');
    const currentAssets = compilation.getAssets().map(i => i.name);
    const lastAssets = await cache.getPromise('assets', null);
    if (lastAssets) {
      for (const asset of currentAssets) {
        if (!lastAssets.includes(asset)) {
          console.log(`New asset: ${asset}`);
        }
      }
    }
    await cache.storePromise('assets', null, currentAssets);
  });
});
```

