TITLE: Configuring HTTPS with file contents in Rspack (CJS)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure HTTPS in Rspack devServer by reading certificate files directly. It uses the `fs` module to read the key, certificate, and CA files, then passes their contents to the `options` object within the `server` configuration. This is a CJS example.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/config/dev-server.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('node:path');

module.exports = {
  //...
  devServer: {
    server: {
      type: 'https',
      options: {
        minVersion: 'TLSv1.1',
        key: fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, './server.key')),
        pfx: fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, './server.pfx')),
        cert: fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, './server.crt')),
        ca: fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, './ca.pem')),
        passphrase: '@rspack/dev-server',
        requestCert: true,
      },
    },
  },
};
```

