TITLE: Conditional Build Configuration using NormalModuleReplacementPlugin
DESCRIPTION: Advanced example demonstrating how to use NormalModuleReplacementPlugin for conditional builds based on environment variables. It replaces a placeholder in the module request with the actual target version.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/plugins/webpack/normal-module-replacement-plugin.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = function getRspackConfig(env) {
  const appTarget = env.APP_TARGET || 'VERSION_A';
  return {
    plugins: [
      new rspack.NormalModuleReplacementPlugin(
        /(.*)-APP_TARGET(\.*)/,
        function (resource) {
          resource.request = resource.request.replace(
            /-APP_TARGET/,
            `-${appTarget}`,
          );
        },
      ),
    ],
  };
};
```

