TITLE: Implementing _create_class Helper Function for Class Creation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This SWC helper function creates a class by defining prototype and static properties on a constructor function. It uses the _defineProperties helper to apply property descriptors to both the constructor's prototype and the constructor itself.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/packages/rspack-test-tools/tests/treeShakingCases/issue-4637/__snapshots__/treeshaking.snap.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function _create_class(Constructor, protoProps, staticProps) {
    if (protoProps) _defineProperties(Constructor.prototype, protoProps);
    if (staticProps) _defineProperties(Constructor, staticProps);

    return Constructor;
}
```

