TITLE: Finding Valid Version for Shared Module in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This function identifies the valid version of a shared module that satisfies the required version criteria. It iterates through available versions and returns the first suitable match that meets the requirements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/module-federation/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var findValidVersion = (scope, key, requiredVersion) => {
    var versions = scope[key];
    var key = Object.keys(versions).reduce((a, b) => {
        if (!satisfy(requiredVersion, b)) return a;
        return !a || versionLt(a, b) ? b : a;
    }, 0);
    return key && versions[key];
};
```

