TITLE: Setting Cache Root for SWC Plugins with Rspack SWC Loader
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures the `cacheRoot` option for SWC plugins within the Rspack SWC loader. It uses the `path` and `fileURLToPath` modules to define a custom cache directory within the `node_modules/.cache/swc` directory. This allows controlling where SWC's cache files are stored, useful for managing project-specific cache locations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/features/builtin-swc-loader.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import path from 'node:path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

const __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));

export default {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.js$/,
        use: {
          loader: 'builtin:swc-loader',
          options: {
            jsc: {
              experimental: {
                cacheRoot: path.join(__dirname, './node_modules/.cache/swc'),
              },
            },
          },
        },
      },
    ],
  },
};
```

