TITLE: Top-Level Stats JSON Structure in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: The top-level structure of the Rspack stats JSON output. This defines the StatsCompilation type which includes information about the compilation process, assets, chunks, modules, and any errors or warnings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/stats-json.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type StatsCompilation = {
  // Fixed simulated webpack version number for compatibility with plugins
  version?: string;
  // Current version number of rspack
  rspackVersion?: string;
  // Compilation name
  name?: string;
  // Compilation specific hash
  hash?: string;
  // Compilation time in milliseconds
  time?: number;
  // Compilation build end timestamp
  builtAt?: number;
  // The `output.publicPath` in the configuration
  publicPath?: string;
  // Path to rspack output directory
  outputPath?: string;
  // Chunk name to emitted asset(s) mapping
  assetsByChunkName?: Record<string, string[]>;
  // List of asset objects, refer to the "Asset Object"
  assets?: StatsAsset[];
  // List of chunk objects, refer to the "Chunk Object"
  chunks?: StatsChunk[];
  // List of module objects, refer to the "Module Object"
