TITLE: Configuring Compilation Logger in Rspack Config
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to configure the logger output level for compilation loggers using stats.logging and stats.loggingDebug settings in the Rspack configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/logger.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  plugins: [{
    apply(compiler) {
      compiler.hooks.thisCompilation.tap("test plugin", compilation => {
        const logger = compilation.getLogger("TEST");
        logger.error("I am an error");
        logger.warn("I am a warning");
        logger.info("I am an information");
        logger.log("I am a log");
        logger.debug("I am a debug log");
      });
    }
  }],
  stats: {
    logging: "verbose",
    loggingDebug: true
  },
};
```

