TITLE: EnvironmentPlugin with Git Version Information in Rspack
DESCRIPTION: Advanced example showing how to use EnvironmentPlugin to include Git version and author date information in the build. It uses child_process to execute Git commands.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/zh/plugins/webpack/environment-plugin.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const child_process = require('child_process');
function git(command) {
  return child_process.execSync(`git ${command}`, { encoding: 'utf8' }).trim();
}

new rspack.EnvironmentPlugin({
  GIT_VERSION: git('describe --always'),
  GIT_AUTHOR_DATE: git('log -1 --format=%aI'),
});
```

