TITLE: Defining additionalTreeRuntimeRequirements Hook in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a custom plugin that adds a runtime module to the webpack's additional tree runtime requirements during the compilation phase. The custom plugin taps into the 'additionalTreeRuntimeRequirements' hook and modifies the runtime requirements set to include the full hash functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/plugin-api/compilation-hooks.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  entry: './index.js',
  plugins: [
    {
      apply(compiler) {
        const { RuntimeGlobals } = compiler.webpack;
        compiler.hooks.thisCompilation.tap('CustomPlugin', compilation => {
          compilation.hooks.additionalTreeRuntimeRequirements.tap(
            'CustomPlugin',
            (_, set) => {
              // add a runtime module which define `__webpack_require__.h`
              set.add(RuntimeGlobals.getFullHash);
            },
          );
        });
      },
    },
  ],
};
