TITLE: Configuring HTTPS with custom options in Rspack
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates configuring HTTPS with custom certificate options within the Rspack devServer. It uses the object syntax for the `server` property to specify the type as 'https' and provide options for certificate paths and passphrase.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/config/dev-server.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  //...
  devServer: {
    server: {
      type: 'https',
      options: {
        ca: './path/to/server.pem',
        pfx: './path/to/server.pfx',
        key: './path/to/server.key',
        cert: './path/to/server.crt',
        passphrase: '@rspack/dev-server',
        requestCert: true,
      },
    },
  },
};
```

