TITLE: Warning Invalid Version Message in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This function generates a user-friendly warning message when the required version of a module is not available in the specified shared scope. It provides a list of available versions to assist developers in debugging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/module-federation/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var getInvalidVersionMessage = (scope, scopeName, key, requiredVersion) => {
    var versions = scope[key];
    return "No satisfying version (" + rangeToString(requiredVersion) + ") of shared module " + key + " found in shared scope " + scopeName + ".\n" +
        "Available versions: " + Object.keys(versions).map((key) => {
            return key + " from " + versions[key].from;
        }).join(", ");
};
```

