TITLE: Webpack Configuration for Custom Parsers
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases the Webpack configuration necessary to parse TOML, YAML, and JSON5 files. It sets up rules for how each file type is handled in the build process. Dependencies include the toml, json5, and yamljs packages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/custom-json-modules/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const toml = require("toml");
const json5 = require("json5");
const yaml = require("yamljs");

module.exports = {
	module: {
		rules: [
			{
				test: /\.toml$/,
				type: "json",
				parser: {
					parse: toml.parse
				}
			},
			{
				test: /\.json5$/,
				type: "json",
				parser: {
					parse: json5.parse
				}
			},
			{
				test: /\.yaml$/,
				type: "json",
				parser: {
					parse: yaml.parse
				}
			}
		]
	}
};
```

