TITLE: Using providePromise for Caching in Rspack Plugin
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the providePromise method to efficiently cache and retrieve asset data in a Rspack plugin. It demonstrates that the data creation function is only called once when using providePromise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/zh/api/javascript-api/cache.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const createAssetsData = async () => {
  console.log('only called once');
  return compilation.getAssets().map(i => i.name);
};

compilation.hooks.processAssets.tapPromise('MyPlugin', async () => {
  const cache = compilation.getCache('MyPlugin');
  console.log(await cache.getPromise('assets', null)); // undefined
  await cache.providePromise('assets', null, createAssetsData); // call createAssetsData
  console.log(await cache.getPromise('assets', null)); // ["main.js"]
  await cache.providePromise('assets', null, createAssetsData); // not call
});
```

