TITLE: User API Module Importing Async Module
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript module `UserApi.js` imports the `dbCall` function from the `db-connection.js` module. The `createUser` function uses `dbCall` to execute a database command. Because it imports an async module that uses top-level await, this module also effectively becomes an async module, requiring asynchronous evaluation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/top-level-await/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { dbCall } from "./db-connection.js";

export const createUser = async name => {
	command = `CREATE USER ${name}`;
	// This is a normal await, because it's in an async function
	await dbCall({ command });
};
```

