TITLE: Working with Etags in Rspack Cache
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use getLazyHashedEtag and mergeEtags for efficient cache identification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/en/api/javascript-api/cache.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const cache = compilation.getCache('MyPlugin');
const dataEtag = cache.getLazyHashedEtag({
  content: 'a'.repeat(10000),
  updateHash(hash) {
    console.log("only called once");
    hash.update(this.content);
  }
});
const mergedEtag = cache.mergeEtags(dataEtag, "other etag");
await cache.storePromise("assets", mergedEtag, "cached value");
console.log(await cache.getPromise("assets", mergedEtag));
```

