TITLE: Conditional Accepting of Module Updates in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows an advanced use case where a module conditionally accepts updates based on the nature of the changes. It uses the 'invalidate' method to bubble up the update when it can't be handled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/website/docs/zh/api/runtime-api/hmr.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { x, y } from './dep';
import { processX, processY } from 'anotherDep';

const oldY = y;

processX(x);
export default processY(y);

module.hot.accept('./dep', () => {
  if (y !== oldY) {
    // 无法处理，冒泡给父级
    module.hot.invalidate();
    return;
  }
  // 可以处理
  processX(x);
});
```

