TITLE: Handling Chunk Loading Errors in Webpack Runtime
DESCRIPTION: Code that handles errors during chunk loading, including setting error properties like message, name, type, and request. It also calls the error callback from the installedChunkData.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/blob/main/tests/webpack-examples/chunkhash/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
if(installedChunkData) {
	var errorType = event && (event.type === 'load' ? 'missing' : event.type);
	var realSrc = event && event.target && event.target.src;
	error.message = 'Loading chunk ' + chunkId + ' failed.\n(' + errorType + ': ' + realSrc + ')';
	error.name = 'ChunkLoadError';
	error.type = errorType;
	error.request = realSrc;
	installedChunkData[1](error);
}
```

